name: Attorney General Eric Schmitt
tweet: This week is National Consumer Protection Week. Below is an overview of the Attorney General's Office's effort to protect consumers from fraud and scams.   Consumers who believe they may have been scammed should file a complaint by calling 800-392-8222.  https://t.co/YNp9sQE3Jl

name: Attorney General Eric Schmitt
tweet: SCAM ALERT: IMPOSTER SCAMS  The Missouri Attorney General's Office is warning consumers about imposter scams. Imposter scams are exactly what they sound like – a con artist posing as someone or something to try and convince you to send them money.  https://t.co/srfqjA2blL

name: Attorney General Eric Schmitt
tweet: Our office charged James M. Enloe for violating Missouri’s Merchandising Practices Act in Greene County. Enloe is charged by complaint with two class E felonies of deceptive business practices in connection with his business, Enloe Exteriors.    https://t.co/mtzCi6bTZV
